quran[21]{c,v,t,f}:
  51,52,"Similarly, there came not to those before them any messenger except that they said, "
  51,53,"Did they suggest it to them?{1} Rather, they [themselves] are a transgressing people.",1:[i.e., Did the former disbelievers pass on these words to the Makkans so that they repeat the same expressions?]
  51,54,"So leave them, [O Muḥammad], for you are not to be blamed."
  52,43,"Or have they a deity other than Allāh? Exalted is Allāh above whatever they associate with Him."
  52,44,"And if they were to see a fragment from the sky falling,{1} they would say, ",1:[Marking the onset of Allāh's punishment, as they had requested.]
  52,45,"So leave them until they meet their Day in which they will be struck insensible -"
  53,37,"And [of] Abraham, who fulfilled [his obligations] -"
  53,38,"That no bearer of burdens will bear the burden of another"
  53,39,"And that there is not for man except that [good] for which he strives"
  54,28,"And inform them that the water is shared between them,{1} each [day of] drink attended [by turn].",1:[i.e., between the tribe of Thamūd and the she-camel - a day for each to drink.]
  54,29,"But they called their companion,{1} and he dared{2} and hamstrung [her].",1:[i.e., the worst and most despicable among them.],2:[Or \"he took,\" referring to his sword or to the she-camel.]
  54,30,"And how [severe] were My punishment and warning."
  55,22,"From both of them emerge pearl and coral."
  55,23,"So which of the favors of your Lord would you deny?"
  55,24,"And to Him belong the ships [with sails] elevated in the sea like mountains."
  56,13,"A [large] company of the former peoples"
  56,14,"And a few of the later peoples,"
  56,15,"On thrones woven [with ornament],"
  57,4,"It is He who created the heavens and earth in six days and then established Himself above the Throne.{1} He knows what penetrates into the earth and what emerges from it and what descends from the heaven and what ascends therein; and He is with you{2} wherever you are. And Allāh, of what you do, is Seeing.",1:[See footnotes to 2:19 and 7:54.],2:[In knowledge - observing and witnessing.]
  57,5,"His is the dominion of the heavens and earth. And to Allāh are returned [all] matters."
  57,6,"He causes the night to enter the day and causes the day to enter the night, and He is Knowing of that within the breasts."
